  {\*\generator Riched20 10.0.17134}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b\f0\fs22 UKMOD Tax Incentives\cf2\b0 : this template provides \ul summary statistics for marginal tax rates (MTRs). MTRs report the effective tax rate applied to the last unit of currency earned. The reported statistics average only over those individuals for whom the MTR was calculated. For example, a population comprised of 100 individuals, might be divided into 10 deciles, each comprised of 10 individuals, ranked in order of ascending household disposable income. If an MTR was calculated for only 3 individuals in the lowest decile, then the respective decile average would be obtained by averaging only over those three individuals.</span></p>
